    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Backlight Updates</h2>
          <h3>Backlight 5.0.4</h3>
          <p>Backlight 5.0.4 released in mid-November, but with holiday inbox madness in full swing, you may have missed it. Here's what's new:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Kookaburra: Adds Custom Stylesheet support</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Adds opt-in grid framework</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Adds PHPlugins support</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Adds sample PHPlugins file to backlight/modules/custom-resources</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Adds Typography and Footer options for text and hyperlink colors</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Cleans up SVG symbols</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Fixes drop-menu shadows</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Removes div.album-copy</li>
            <li>Kookaburra: Replaces CDN Fancybox assets with local copies</li>
            <li>Kookaburra &amp; Pangolin: Improves cookies acceptance notice in iOS Safari</li>
            <li>Kookaburra &amp; Pangolin: Tweaks styling of cookies acceptance buttons</li>
            <li>Pangolin: In client response templates, only display slideshow Select/Feedback icons if Client Response features are enabled for the album</li>
            <li>Maintenance: Deletes unnecessary instance of normalize.css</li>
            <li>Adds fix for PHP compatibility in phpLiteAdmin</li>
            <li>Changes behavior of Smart Albums to allow the use of private keywords</li>
            <li>Changes behavior of Smart Albums to include protected photos when logged in to public albums that allow the display of protected photos</li>
            <li>Fixes issue of LR-protected photos not being filtered out in Smart Albums</li>
            <li>Fixes issue of lights-out images not being filtered out for Client Response albums</li>
            <li>Fixes issue with Access Codes not working if they include special characters including ampersands</li>
          </ul>

          <p>See our video walkthrough, <a href="https://blog.theturninggate.net/2018/09/12/installing-updates-in-backlight-2/">How-to: Installing Updates in Backlight</a>.</p>

          <h3>Work-in-progress</h3>
          <p>The next Backlight update is in the works, and will hit maybe before the end of December, or maybe sometime after the new year. It's shaping up to be doozy.</p>
          <p>For Kookaburra, I am jazzing up the slideshow with customizations, customization options, and lots of improvements, while also setting the stage for future enhancements.</p>
          <p>There are shortcodes coming that should give you more control over content being displayed to users, based on whether they are logged in or out.</p>
          <p>And there are some new RSS feeds in the works that will give us magical powers!</p>
          <p>Keep an eye on the blog for the release announcement.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
