    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>The **NEW** Best Way to Include Google Fonts</h2>
          <p>The EU came down hard on Google Fonts this year. As a result, we are changing our recommendation for how to use Google Fonts in a Backlight site.</p>
          <p>The old way to include Google Fonts in Okapi and Pangolin is being deprecated. Not removed, because that would be a breaking change to existing sites; we don't want to do that.</p>
          <p>The new way, in TL; DR format is, download the fonts you want, upload them to Backlight's custom folder, then use a custom stylesheet to declare them. You can then use them by name in Backlight's designer.</p>
          <p>For full details, see this new article I've published:</p>
          <p><a href="https://backlight.me/docs/google-fonts">Using Google Fonts in Backlight</a></p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-section>
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text css-class="article">
          <h2>Obsidian, Your New Markdown Editor</h2>
          <p>A new Markdown editor available on Mac, Windows and Linux, and iOS and Android, <a href="https://obsidian.md/">Obsidian</a> is free (forever!) for personal use, and seems ideally suited to the needs of Backlight users.</p>
          <p>Documents are organized into "vaults", quickly accessible via the sidebar, and an encrypted sync keeps things up-to-date between devices.</p>
          <p>On disk, a vault is just a folder, containing nested folders and Markdown documents. I love this, because should I ever choose to leave Obsidian, I still have my files, and they can be opened in any text or Markdown editor. They're not in some proprietary format, they're not locked away in a database.</p>
          <p>The app is also highly extensible, with roughly 750 community extensions currently listed on their website.</p>
          <p>See <a href="https://obsidian.md/">the Obsidian website</a> for more information, but definitely give Obsidian a look.</p>
        </mj-text>        
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

